## Proposed Changes

### Backend

#### [MODIFY] [AuthDTO.cs](file:///c:/Users/ACER/Desktop/Ky%208/EXE102/innerg/api/InnerG.Api/DTOs/AuthDTO.cs)
Add new DTOs:
- `InviteListItemResponse` ‚Äî list item with inviterName, departmentName, computed status
- `InviteListQuery` ‚Äî page, pageSize, status, search

#### [MODIFY] [IAuthService.cs](file:///c:/Users/ACER/Desktop/Ky%208/EXE102/innerg/api/InnerG.Api/Services/Interfaces/IAuthService.cs)
Add interface methods:
- `Task<PaginatedResponse<InviteListItemResponse>> GetInvitesAsync(InviteListQuery query, Guid companyId, bool isSystemAdmin)`
- `Task<ValidateFileResult> ValidateInviteFileAsync(IFormFile file, Guid companyId)`

#### [MODIFY] [AuthService.cs](file:///c:/Users/ACER/Desktop/Ky%208/EXE102/innerg/api/InnerG.Api/Services/Implementations/AuthService.cs)
Implement the 2 new methods:
- `GetInvitesAsync` ‚Äî query [Invites](file:///c:/Users/ACER/Desktop/Ky%208/EXE102/innerg/api/InnerG.Api/Services/Implementations/AuthService.cs#219-239) with IgnoreQueryFilters, include Inviter + Department, compute EXPIRED status in-memory (ExpiresAt < NOW && Status == PENDING)
- `ValidateInviteFileAsync` ‚Äî parse CSV/Excel rows, validate each (email format, domain, existing user, pending invite), return valid/invalid lists

> **Library for Excel parsing**: Use `ExcelDataReader` or `CsvHelper` NuGet package. Will use `CsvHelper` for CSV + `ExcelDataReader` for .xlsx, keeping simple approach with manual extension check.

#### [MODIFY] [AuthController.cs](file:///c:/Users/ACER/Desktop/Ky%208/EXE102/innerg/api/InnerG.Api/Controllers/AuthController.cs)
Add:
- `GET /api/auth/invites` ‚Äî list with pagination/filters, `[Authorize(Roles = "HR,SystemAdmin")]`
- `POST /api/auth/invites/validate-file` ‚Äî multipart upload, `[Authorize(Roles = "HR,SystemAdmin")]`

